<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900510-0107</DOCNO><DOCID>900510-0107.</DOCID><HL>   California Energy Gets Loan</HL><DATE>05/10/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   CE CHV</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   SAN FRANCISCO -- California Energy Co. said it completedfinancing for its agreement to buy certain geothermaloperations of Chevron Resource Co.   The company said it received a $35 million, six-yearunsecured term loan from Credit Suisse Bank and NationalWestminster Bank.</LP><TEXT>   California Energy agreed to acquire the properties of theChevron Corp. unit in Oregon, Utah and Nevada for $68.7million. The geothermal company said it is arranging anadditional loan for a subsidiary to operate the acquiredproperties.</TEXT></DOC>